Hmph!"
Vopral's ire is palatiable across the channel as he acknowledged
Darkfate's respond. "I will contact you later. Have your report ready!"
The channel closed with an audible click.

Meanwhile Marauder -
the subject of Vorpral's interest - floated in the air seeming to
examine the region. Within a few moments a slow rumble could be heard
as birds rose into the air and animals bellowed in fear as they reacted
to sudden seismic activity. The once calm, icy blue
water water of the lake rippled and then splashed as the activity
became more forceful. 

Then with an ugly hissing sound, smoke
began billowing from the cave entrance that the minions had just exited
from, the smell of sulfur filling the once pristine air. 

"Yess,
indeed." Marauder said softly as he watched the show! Still in his
starfighter mode he banked almost lazily away from the distant mountains as he activated his boosters. "Come my minions! We will soon
subjugate this ball of rock!" Marauder said as he began to chuckle
lightly to himself. "But first we will need an army!"

He began
to move off to the south, away from scene, away from the mountains, and
onto the new beginnings of the Minion menace on the Earth. 

Behind
him magma began spewing out of the cave entrance as it fell steaming
into the water below, looking like a molten water
fall. White steam and vapors billowed into the air as the water was quickly boiled away by the lava.

Marauder began to laugh as he picked up speed!

Preston
